From: Barry Jackson <barjac@mageia.org>
Date: Mon, 15 Jun 2026 11:56:58 +0100
Subject: [PATCH 1/2] Hamlib: auto-reconnect to rigctld after broken pipe

When the hamlib connection to rigctld is lost (e.g. radio powered off
and rigctld restarted on the remote host), FreeDV now recovers without
requiring the modem to be stopped and restarted:

- On hitting the error threshold in requestCurrentFrequencyModeImpl_(),
  the broken hamlib handle is closed, onRigDisconnected is fired, and a
  reconnecting_ flag is set with a 5-second back-off timestamp.
- The existing 1-second ID_TIMER_UPD_FREQ timer continues to call
  requestCurrentFrequencyMode() (isConnected() guard removed); when the
  handle is null and the back-off has elapsed, connectImpl_() is called.
- connectImpl_() suppresses error dialogs during reconnect attempts and
  updates nextReconnectAt_ on each failure; on success it clears
  reconnecting_ and fires onRigConnected() so the UI resumes normally.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Sonnet 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>
